7:
Not a single one of our forces
survived?
9: Yes. But it was a necessary sacrifice.
11:
I understand that the only path to
Pandemonium lies under the
Doomsday Lance...
14:
But is it wise to keep sending our
soldiers to their death? Is it not our
duty to protect the people of this
country—
17:
Exactly! You see how our little waves
are dashed against the fiend's
troops like foam against a seawall. I
say we double—no, triple the
fighters we march in!
19:
The beastfolk are clamoring to join
the war. With them, we can swell our
numbers and morale.
21:
Why not?! Is it not a beast's job to
hunt?
23:
Fear not, Princess! We are as ready
to lay down our lives as any of our
soldiers in the field!
26:
But what of our people? What of the
innocent folk who have been
pushed from their homes?
29: That, too, will be a necessary—
33:
There is a large number of civilians
heading in our direction!
35: What?! How did they find us?
36:
W-well... They are being led by
Shakari, sir.
38: Princess, let's not be hasty... Princess!
42: Why can you not let us pass?
44:
I-I'm sorry! But it's just that we've
never let in so many at once!
48:
I carry out Lilith's will. Tell me, who do
you serve?
57: I am glad to see you safe.
61:
The forces stationed at Sabre Peak
were eradicated.
63:
I was only able to extract the
civilians.
67:
That is already more than I dared
hope for. Thank you, Shakari.
71:
Many are sick or injured. See that
they are cared for.
82:
No. She is someone else... But the
resemblance...
91:
Ah, Shakari! I see you have escaped
death yet again!
93:
Well, well... That really is quite a flock
you've herded to our gates.
95:
Yes... I'm not certain that we can
procure quarters for all of them.
97:
So you're gonna leave 'em out in the
cold?
101:
They came all this way, believing
you'd help them. You can't just—
106:
How can we restore the royal family
of Stratos to its former glory if we
abandon its people?
110:
Surely, you are not foolish enough to
suggest such a thing.
114:
I shall make the proper
arrangements... yet again.
116:
Ahem. Shakari, I must ask that you
provide us with a full report. And
please... Keep in mind that you are
our strongest warrior. Do not
endanger your life needlessly.
118:
Now, Princess. Shall we return to the
Chamber?
121:
Wait. I must say a few words about
the strangers I bring with me. They
risked life and limb to guide our
people to safety. They are worthy of
your trust.
125:
Travelers. As the sole survivor of the
royal family of Stratos, I offer you my
thanks.
128:
A country's greatest treasure is its
people. I am in your debt.
133:
Not at all. We were just helping each
other out!
137: You need not bow to us!
141:
We shall meet after I have
performed my duties. Until then.
146:
Come on. I don't know about you,
but my paws are killin' me.
